```text
# Example env files for local development (DO NOT commit real secrets)

# 1) Backend: copy this into backend/.env
#    Windows PowerShell: copy contents into a new file at backend\.env
PORT=5000

# Azure OpenAI (leave blank for mock mode)
AZURE_OPENAI_KEY=
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=gpt-4o-mini
AZURE_REGION=

# Azure Cognitive Services (Translator / Speech)
COGNITIVE_KEY=
COGNITIVE_ENDPOINT=
COGNITIVE_REGION=

# 2) Frontend: copy this into a top-level .env or frontend/.env (Vite expects VITE_ prefix)
#    Example (create file at project root: .env)
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# Instructions:
# - Copy the "Backend" block into backend/.env before running the backend locally.
# - Copy the "Frontend" line into .env at the project root before running the frontend.
# - Keep these files out of version control (they are covered by .gitignore).
```